text: Eugenia uxpanapensis is a species of plant in the family Myrtaceae. It is endemic to the Uxpanapa region of Veracruz state in eastern Mexico. ==References== uxpanapensis Category:Endemic flora of Mexico Category:Trees of Veracruz Category:Endangered biota of Mexico Category:Endangered flora of North America Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
